description:
Description

imPRESS ready-to-wear press-on nails look natural, take minutes to apply, and stay perfect for up to 7 days. Just press on and go!
•	No glue needed, chip proof, smudge proof, waterproof and no dry time
•	On-trend mixed pastel fashion nails are medium length amd coffin shaped
•	Kit contains 30 Press-on Nails, Prep Pad, Mini Nail File, and Manicure Stick


Suggested Use

PREPARATION:
1.	Prior to application, align nails with tab sides facing your cuticles and find correct size for each nail.
2.	When you are in between sizes go smaller, not larger.
3.	Wash hands with soap and water and dry thoroughly.
4.	Use included cuticle stick to push back any excess skin.
5.	Wipe nails with the enclosed prep pad to clean nails for better adhesion. You can use rubbing alcohol in place of or in addition to prep pad.
APPLICATION:
1.	Peel backing from nail then press it down on your natural nail, in the center and at both sides at the same time.
2.	Hold for 30 seconds. (Press on thumbnails last.)
3.	If there is exposed adhesive, brush clear nail polish between your nail and the imPRESS and press down.
4.	Wait at least an hour to wet hands or file nails if desired.
REMOVAL:
1.	Trim and file surface to disrupt protective top coat.
2.	Use KISS Glue OFF, or soak nails in acetone polish remover until soft.
3.	Wipe off softened nails and adhesive. Do not force or pull nails off.

Ingredients

Nails: ABS Plastic - Made in Vietnam. 
Adhesive: Acrylic Acid, Ethylhexyl Acrylate, Hydroxycyclohexyl Phenyl Ketone - Made in Korea.

reviews.title: Primadonna Nail Strips
reviews.content: Sigh I hate to leave an average review but this particular nail set was average at best. The gem included is super hard to adhere as a sticker due to the curvature of the nail bed and often there are air bubbles on the side which do not look pretty especially when it’s set with the curing light. I’m extremely disappointed with EDGEU for reformulating their gel stickers because they reduce the number of stickers available compared to the old version - you might not find a sticker which fits your nail. Bring back the old version please.
